Ocular acicle terminating in two to five spines, or rarely one. Anterodorsal plate of branchiostegite smooth, at most with one to two spinules subproximally.Upper margin of right chela smooth (
Fig. 1D
). Outer face of left chela regularly convex (
Fig. 1C
). Dactyls of P2-P3 with similar setation consisting of sparse, widely-spaced tufts of setae (
Fig. 1E
). Propodus of P3 with dorsolateral margin weakly angled; upper half of outer face slightly concave, forming faint sulcus. Dactyl of P3 0.6-0.7 times length of propodus, with six to eight small spines on ventral margin.Telson with posterior lobes each with single terminal spine.

